snippet.textDisplay:
This is the interpretation of the emblem:

In the old testament of the Bible, while the Jews were in the wilderness, the people complained about Moses and God and their situation. Well because the people were turning from God, they stepped out of his protection and then deadly snakes would bite the the people. Well God basically said to make a replica of a snake and hang it on a pole and whoever looks at the replica in faith would be healed (Numbers 21:4-9).

Well the cross is representing Jesus. And the the person being spit out by the snake as a new man is the representation of the healing and new life that provided by Jesus being sacrificed on the cross (Isaiah 53:4-6).
